        <num>CC 3426</num>
        <heading>3426.  Constructive possession</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3426.  Constructive possession
One who possesses a part of an immovable by virtue of a title is deemed to have constructive possession within the limits of his title.  In the absence of title, one has possession only of the area he actually possesses.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=110449</p>
